r s BC-BBA-ANGELS-NOTEBOOK-L     05-19 0335
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBA-ANGELS-NOTEBOOK-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE GOOD AND BAD BEHIND COMEBACKS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 c.2000 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. _ Eight of the Angels' 20 victories this season
are come-from-behind wins, which can be a good thing and a bad
thing, according to manager Mike Scioscia.
</P>
<P>
   The good thing about it is the Angels never feel they are out of
any game. Last month in Toronto, they rallied from an 11-1 deficit
only to lose 12-11.
</P>
<P>
   But Scioscia said falling behind early in games is a bad habit
to get into because it can put an added strain on the hitters.
</P>
<P>
   ``If we're going to reach our potential, we're going to have to
do a better job of shutting down clubs early in the game,'' he
said. ``Catching up is nice, but it can only take you so far. How
many times are you going to come back against a (Mike) Timlin or a
(John) Wetteland?
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously, we're not setting up our game plan saying, `Let's
hold 'em to five or six runs in the first four innings, then come
back and get 'em.' I have a tremendous amount of confidence in our
starting pitchers. Certainly our depth has been tested. But we have
enough to get us where we want to be.''
</P>
<P>
   CLOSER CLARIFICATION: Scioscia has been hesitant to use closer
Troy Percival in non-save situations, but he made an exception
Wednesday night when Percival entered the game in the top of the
ninth and the game tied at 7.
</P>
<P>
   Even though Percival walked three batters in the inning, it
worked out. The Orioles didn't score and the Angels scored in the
bottom of the ninth on Scott Spiezio's RBI single to win it 8-7.
</P>
<P>
   ``Percival will pitch the ninth inning in home games that are
tied,'' Scioscia said. ``But it depends on where the other
relievers are at the time, because I have just as much confidence
in (Shigetoshi) Hasegawa and (Mark) Petkovsek as Percival.''
</P>
<P>
   Unlike past Angels managers, Scioscia will not use Percival on
the road unless it's a save situation. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
