<P>
   RAC-PREAKNESS-SEKIGUCHI (Baltimore) _ A look at Fusao Sekiguchi,
the flamboyant Japanese entrepreneur who only two weeks ago was a
stranger to the American sporting scene but who prompted
fascination at the Kentucky Derby with his long ponytail and
splashy entrance _ accompanied by four incandescently powdered
geishas _ to the winner's circle at Churchill Downs. By Joe Drape
and Howard W. French.
