   AIR-FORCE-GAY (San Francisco) _ They didn't ask, but John
Hensala decided to tell anyway. The San Francisco resident believed
that to serve in the Air Force as a psychiatrist, he had to be
honest about his homosexuality _ a decision that led to an
honorable discharge in 1997. More than three years later, Hensala
claims the military is going against its own regulations, trying to
recoup more than $71,000 in scholarship funds from him even though
he was more than willing to stay in the service. By PETER HARTLAUB.
