yourself wearing jailhouse orange at the end of the day. The annual
Examiner Bay to Breakers run, which will be held Sunday, is famous
'round the world for the goofy costumes its participants wear. But
each year a growing number of the race's 80,000-plus runners shed
their costumes and hit the road wearing nothing more than running
shoes, socks and, maybe, a baseball cap. By JIM HERRON ZAMORA.
