</P>
<P>
   TAIWAN-INAUG (Taipei) _ A new president is to be sworn in
Saturday morning (Friday night, New York time), the first ever from
the opposition and one China is watching and threatening because of
his past indepedence views. By Erik Eckholm.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-TRADE-EUROPE (Shanghai) _ China and the European Union
agree on market access deal, further paving the way for China to
join World Trade Organization. By Craig. S. Smith.
</P>
<P>
   PERU-ELECTION (Lima) _ Political developments in advance of the
Fujimori-Toledo presidential runoff. By Clifford Krauss.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-PALESTINIANS (Dateline to kum) _ Folo on reports that an
Israeli and a Palestinian have been killed in gun battles in Gaza.
By Deborah Sontag.
</P>
<P>
   ETHIOPIA-ERITREA (Barentu, Eritrea) _ A report from a city
captured by the Ethiopian Army. By Ian Fisher.
</P>
<P>
   SIERRA-LEONE-U.N. (United Nations) _ The Security Council
increases the size of the Sierra Leone peacekeeping force, and it
may increase it again next week. By Barbara Crossette.
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-BRIEFS (Various datelines) _ Short news items from around
the world.
