<P>
   From the Saturday Ideas Page:
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-TRADE-EXPERTS (Undated) _ Intellectuals and others who
make up the American ``strategic class'' are suddenly focusing
their attention on China. Yet unlike traditional sinologists, who
have made a broad study of China's complex history and culture,
this new crop of experts are preoccupied with a much narrower
question: will China be our next enemy? Within the circumscribed
world of strategists, this sharpened approach is stirring bitter
debates over how to interpret China, while in the larger political
arena it is having an impact on pressing policy debates in
Washington, including next week's congressional vote on China's
trade status. By Kurt M. Campbell.
</P>
