seven astronauts head for a rendezvous with the international space
station, where the crew will make repairs. By MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
   BEARS-DNA (Glacier National Park, Mont.) _ Clever scientists
have come up with a new grizzly bear census in Glacier National
Park by using DNA in bear hairs. Based on the new technique, the
bear counters estimate that there are 332 grizzlies in the park,
located in Northwestern Montana. By comparison, a 1970 census based
on bear sightings came up with an estimate of 200 bears in the
park. By The Hearst Newspapers. (Already filed.)
</P>
