Association should be an outfit on its heels. Mothers are marching
against it, and the Democrats are using it as a perpetual punching
bag. But on the floor of the Charlotte Coliseum, where the gun
owner's group is gathering for its annual convention, the attitude
is one of defiance. By James Dao.
</P>
