<P>
   PEACEKEEPING-U.S. (Washington) _ Sen. Judd Gregg, R-N.H., has
singlehandedly blocked the United States from paying $368 million
that it owes the United Nations for four of its most difficult
peacekeeping operations, infuriating the Clinton Administration and
some of its allies. The dispute is the latest flareup in a running
battle between the administration, which has tried to use American
power and money abroad in operations other than war, and a
Republican-led Congress that increasingly disdains those missions.
This is a little-known and entirely informal process in which
appropriated money can be put on hold, like a nomination, by
strong-arming and jawboning. By Tim Weiner.
</P>
<P>
   1-column hed.
</P>
