<P>
   ALA-CHURCH-BOMBING (Birmingham, Ala.) _ As they waited for the
other shoe to drop, the men accused of bombing Birmingham's 16th
Street Baptist Church have gone about their lives for the last 37
years. Thomas E. Blanton Jr. has worked as a security guard and
Wal-Mart clerk (in sporting goods, selling guns and ammo) while
living in a dilapidated trailer on property in Birmingham owned by
another former Klansman. Bobby Frank Cherry worked as a truck
driver in Mabank, Texas, while fending off accusations about his
role in the bombing made by a string of ex-wives and other
relatives. By Kevin Sack.
</P>
<P>
   3-column hed.
</P>
