<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-QUADRIPLEGIC-GRAD-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 16)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 16,
about Brooke Ellison, a quadriplegic who is to graduate from
Harvard next month, included an erroneous surmise from the
university about the achievement. Harvard now says Ellison is not
the first such graduate; it has identified two other quadriplegics
who earned bachelor's degrees.
</P>
<P>
   BC-ETHIOPIA-ERITREA-NYT (moved on Thursday, May 18)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, May 18,
about the war between Ethiopia and Eritrea misstated the title of
Ethiopia's leader, Meles Zenawi. He is prime minister, not
president.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CAMPAIGN-BRIEFS-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 16)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 16,
referred incorrectly in some copies to a scheduled appearance by
Senator John McCain with Senator Spencer Abraham, Republican of
Michigan. McCain was never scheduled to appear with Abraham.  &QL; 
