to protest Israel's refusal to release Palestinian security
prisoners. (Rina Castelnuovo/The New York Times) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) RAMALLAH, West Bank -- May 19, 2000 --
MIDEAST-PALESTINIANS -- Hundreds of Palestinians hurled stones at
Israeli troops Friday in several clashes across Palestinian areas
to protest Israel's refusal to release Palestinian security
prisoners at this time. In the town of Ramallah in the West Bank,
demonstrators burned an effigy of Barak and a U.S. flag, then
headed to a traffic circle on the outskirts of town to throw stones
at soldiers who fired rubber bullets. (Rina Castelnuovo/The New
York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- May 19, 2000 -- NY-SCOOTERS -- Newly endowed
with Rollerblade-style wheels, snowboard decks and aircraft-quality
steel frames, human powered scooters, propelled by scuffing foot
against pavement, have shot to the top of the sales catalogs.
Scooter riders on the town. (Vincent Laforet/The New York Times)
LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) UNDATED -- May 19, 2000 -- OBIT-KAZAN -- Michael Kazan,
who gave society and entertainment figures the bouffant hairdo and
created the coiffures for the models of several fashion designers,
died Saturday in New York. Kazan, left, and one of his bouffant
styles from 1963. (The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
